William Edward Sawyer was an American inventor whose contribution was pimarily in the field of electric engineering and electric lighting. 

His primary inventions include:<br />
Telegraph apparatus for cable use - Mar 31, 1874<br />
Automatic and autographic telegraph and circuit - Feb 2, 1875<br />
Electric engineering and lighting apparatus and system - Aug 14, 1877<br />
Device for effecting the static discharge in autographic telegraphy - Nov 6, 1877<br />
Electric switch - Jun 29, 1880<br />
Electrical safety device for elevators - Jul 6, 1880
